'''''MetLife Inc. v. Financial Stability Oversight Council''''' is a 2016 case that challenged the [[systemically important financial institution]] rules in [[Dodd-Frank]]. U.S. District Judge  Rosemary Collyer ruled that MetLife could shed its Sifi designation, after concluding FSOC's designation was "arbitrary and capricious". FSOC subsequently launched an appeal but decided to drop the case in January 2018. [http://www.nationallawjournal.com/id=1202754350078/Document-MetLife-v-Financial-Stability-Oversight-Council?slreturn=20160307152900]

